{"word":"κωμῳδέω","slug":"κωμῳδέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κωμῳδέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κωμῳδός'><el>κωμῳδός</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to represent in a comedy, to satirise, lampoon, libel</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be so satirised</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><el>κωμωιδεῖν τὰ δίκαια  κωμωιδοῦντα εἰπεῖν τὰ δ.</el>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to write comedies</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}